Nvidia is being accused... again... of trying to bury coverage of their more budget-friendly GPUs. This time, they allegedly withheld RTX 5060 drivers from reviewers until launch day, which just so happens to fall on the first day of Computex. Linus and Luke talk about Nvidia’s strange priorities, whether GeForce should be spun off, and why Intel's Battle Mage might be more important than people think.
